WARNING:LINE_SPACING: Missing a blank line after declarations
#154: FILE: arch/x86/kernel/ptrace.c:665:
+	struct bts_context *context = kzalloc(sizeof(*context), GFP_KERNEL);
+	if (context) {

Vertical space is wasted given the limited number of lines an
editor window can display when multiple blank lines are used.

See: https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/latest/process/coding-style.html#spaces

CHECK:UNNECESSARY_PARENTHESES: Unnecessary parentheses around 'cfg.size != context->size'
#296: FILE: arch/x86/kernel/ptrace.c:785:
+	if ((cfg.flags & PTRACE_BTS_O_ALLOC) && (cfg.size != context->size)) {

Parentheses are not required in the following cases:

  1. Function pointer uses::

      (foo->bar)();

    could be::

      foo->bar();

  2. Comparisons in if::

      if ((foo->bar) && (foo->baz))
      if ((foo == bar))

    could be::

      if (foo->bar && foo->baz)
      if (foo == bar)

  3. addressof/dereference single Lvalues::

      &(foo->bar)
      *(foo->bar)

    could be::

      &foo->bar
      *foo->bar

WARNING:LIKELY_MISUSE: nested (un)?likely() calls, IS_ERR already uses unlikely() internally
#321: FILE: arch/x86/kernel/ptrace.c:803:
+	if (unlikely(IS_ERR(context->tracer))) {

CHECK:AVOID_EXTERNS: extern prototypes should be avoided in .h files
#494: FILE: include/linux/mm.h:1322:
+extern void refund_locked_buffer_memory(struct mm_struct *mm, size_t size);

Function prototypes don't need to be declared extern in .h
files.  It's assumed by the compiler and is unnecessary.

